<headline>Winter Weather Advisory issued January 07 at 2:46AM MST until January 08 at 3:00AM MST by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY FOR BLOWING SNOW REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 1
PM THIS AFTERNOON TO 3 AM MST SATURDAY...
...WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY FOR SNOWFALL IS CANCELLED...
* WHAT...Snow has ended...therefore the winter weather advisory has
been cancelled. Blowing snow expected. Winds gusting as high as 45
mph this afternoon.
* WHERE...Fergus and Chouteau Counties.
* WHEN...From 1 PM this afternoon to 3 AM MST Saturday.
* IMPACTS...Areas of blowing snow could significantly reduce
visibility.</description>
<instruction>Use caution while traveling, especially in open areas. The latest
road conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1 or visiting the MDT
Road Report website.</instruction>
